
                    Resource Bundles

1. Resource bundles contain locale-specific data.

2. They take the format of a map with keys and values. The
   values are locale-specific.

3. Resource bundles can be created in 2 ways:
    - java files -> extend ListResourceBundle
    - property files -> text files with key value pairs



                    Property files:

 1. Simple text files in the format of key=value pairs ( or key:value pairs).
    The property files therefore, follow very specific naming conventions.
    Keys and values are both Strings e.i. Map<String,String>

 2. The suffix is .properties

 3. ResourceBundle.getBundle(name,[locale]) loads the relevant property file.

